<h3 id=u.9.5.1a><a
href="/TR/2010/WD-CSS2-20101207/visuren.html#float-position">9.5.1
Positioning the float: the 'float' property</a></h3>

<p>Because of lack of sufficient implementations, the top of a
floating box is allowed to be above the top of earlier boxes in
certain difficult cases. Add after the numbered list:

<blockquote>
<p><ins>But in CSS&nbsp;2.1, if, within the block formatting context,
there is an in-flow negative vertical margin such that the float's
position is above the position it would be at were all such negative margins
set to zero, the position of the float is undefined.</ins>
</blockquote>

