href="/TR/2010/WD-CSS2-20101207/visuren.html#positioning-scheme">9.3
Positioning schemes</a></h3>

<p>Add formal definitions of the terms &ldquo;out of flow,&rdquo;
&ldquo;in-flow&rdquo; and &ldquo;flow of an element&rdquo;:

<blockquote>
<p><ins>An element is called <dfn>out of flow</dfn> if it is floated,
absolutely positioned, or is the root element. An element is called
<dfn>in-flow</dfn> if it is not out-of-flow. The <dfn>flow of an
element</dfn> <var>A</var> is the set consisting of <var>A</var> and
all in-flow elements whose nearest out-of-flow ancestor is
<var>A</var>.</ins>
